ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class CallClearedEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.CallClearedEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class CallClearedEvent
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable

    Indicates that all devices have been removed from an existing call. The Call Cleared event is only provided for calls that are being call-type monitored. This event indicates that a call has been cleared and no longer exists within the switching sub-domain.

    The only supported parameters for the CallClearedEvent are:

    CallClearedEvent Supported Parameters
    monitorCrossRefID Mandatory Associates the event to an established monitor.
    clearCall Mandatory Specifies the ConnectionID of the cleared call.
    cause Mandatory Specifies the reason for the event.
    extensions optional CallClearedEventPrivateData object that contains the following field:
    • reason - Specifies the reason for this event

    EventCause values:

    • BUSY: Device is busy.
    • CALLCANCELLED: Call rejected or cancelled.
    • DESTNOTOBTAINABLE: Called device is not reachable or wrong number is called.
    • CALLNOTANSWERED: Called device not responding or call not answered (maxRings timed out) for a MakePredictiveCall.
    • NETWORKCONGESTION: Network congestion or channel is unacceptable.
    • RESOURCESNOTAVAILABLE: No circuit or channel is available.
    • TRANSFER: Call merged due to transfer or conference.
    • REORDERTONE: Intercept treatment - Number changed.
    • MAKEPREDICTIVECALL: Answer machine is detected for a MakePredictiveCall.

    CSTA Functional Requirements:

    1. A ConnectionClearedEvent will be sent for all devices in the call before the Call Cleared event is sent. The Call Cleared event can not be used as a substitute for the appropriate Connection Cleared events.
    2. The Call Cleared event is only sent to call-type monitors. It is never sent to device-type monitors.

    Private Data:

    CallClearedEventPrivateData Parameters
    reason CallClearedReason Specifies the reason for this event.

    Reason Values:

    • none - no value specified for reason
    • answerNormal - Answer supervision from the network or internal answer
    • answerTimed - Assumed answer based on internal timer
    • answerVoiceEnergy - Voice energy detection from a call classifier
    • answerMachineDetected - Answering machine detected
    • reorder - Switch equipment congestion
    • noCircuit - No circuit or channel available
    • intercept - Number changed
    • unassignedNumber - Unassigned number
    • invalidNumber - Invalid number
    • unknown - Normal unspecified
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
